## üîß How It Works

The project uses a predefined object `profileDetails`:

```javascript
const profileDetails = {
  name: "John Doe",
  imgSrc: "https://example.com/profile.jpg",
  age: "28 years old"
};
```

From this, JavaScript dynamically creates:

* A heading element for the name
* An image element for the profile picture
* A paragraph element for the age

All these are appended as children to the container with the ID `profileContainer`.

---

## üìù Notes

* Prefilled code must remain untouched.
* The layout and styles aim to match the provided design reference.
* This project reinforces dynamic DOM handling, useful for real-world applications like user dashboards or content feeds.

